Weblogic


https://www.oracle.com/middleware/technologies/weblogic-server-installers-downloads.html



https://www.oracle.com/middleware/technologies/weblogic-server-installers-downloads.html
Download:
Generic Installer for Oracle WebLogic Server and Oracle Coherence:
Oracle WebLogic Server and Coherence (655 MB)


Once downloaded,
Start the installer, it will download a .zip file 
Unzip the file
We get a jar file as:
fmw_14.1.2.0.0_wls.jar
Open cmd as administrator
Go to the folder where .jar is kept
Run
> java –jar fmw_14.1.2.0.0_wls.jar
The GUI installer opens → choose:
Oracle Home (e.g., C:\Oracle\Middleware)
Select “WebLogic Server” component
Proceed with installation.


After installation, you’ll see:
C:\Oracle\Middleware\Oracle_Home\
 ├── wlserver\
 ├── coherence\
 └── oracle_common\



Create a New Domain
Run the Configuration Wizard or it will run the wizard automatically post installation:
cd C:\Oracle\Middleware\Oracle_Home\wlserver\common\bin
config.cmd
Steps:
Create a new domain
Choose Basic WebLogic Server Domain
Set credentials (username: weblogic, password: Webl0gic)
Select JDK (choose your installed JDK)
Choose optional components (Admin Server, Managed Server, etc.)
Finish and save the domain (e.g., C:\Oracle\Middleware\user_projects\domains\mydomain)


We get the C drive as:
C:\Users\Monica\AppData\Local\Temp\OraInstall2025-10-07_10-36-07PM>

You should have WebLogic installed at something like:
cd C:\Oracle\Middleware\Oracle_Home\wlserver


Run the Configuration Wizard:
cd C:\Oracle\Middleware\Oracle_Home\wlserver\common\bin
config.cmd
Steps:
Create a new domain
Choose Basic WebLogic Server Domain
Set credentials (username: weblogic, password: Webl0gic)
Select JDK (choose your installed JDK)
Choose optional components (Admin Server, Managed Server, etc.)
Finish and save the domain (e.g., C:\Oracle\Middleware\user_projects\domains\mydomain)



To start the Admin Server:
cd C:\Oracle\Middleware\Oracle_Home\user_projects\domains\base_domain
startWebLogic.cmd
Wait until you see:
..<Server state changed to RUNNING>
Then open your browser and visit:
http://localhost:7001/console
Log in using:
Username: weblogic
Password: Webl0gic


For Weblogic 14.1.2+
Download the remote Console:
https://github.com/oracle/weblogic-remote-console/releases
Download 
WebLogic-Remote-Console-2.4.17-win.exe
Once Installed
Open Remote Weblogic app from start menu
Choose Add Admin..
Give a name to the Connection: weblogic11
Give credentials



Create a PrjhelloJsp in Eclipse as a dynamic web project with Web Module Version: 4.0
Add index.jsp page


<%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html; charset=UTF-8" pageEncoding="UTF-8"%>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Welcome to WebLogic JSP App</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Hello from WebLogic JSP Application!</h2>
    <p>This is your index.jsp deployed on WebLogic 14.1.2.</p>
</body>
</html>









<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<web-app xmlns="http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee
                             http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee/web-app_4_0.xsd"
         version="4.0">

    <display-name>PrjJsp</display-name>

    <welcome-file-list>
        <welcome-file>index.jsp</welcome-file>
    </welcome-file-list>

</web-app>







